n.'' London: Vintage Press. {{ISBN|978-0-09-952709-1}}.\n* Myers, A. R. (1978) ''England in the Late Middle Ages.'' Harmondsworth: Penguin Books.\n* Neillands, Robin. (2001) ''The Hundred Years War.'' London: Routledge.\n* Sumption, Jonathan. (1999) ''The Hundred Years War: Trial by Battle.'' Philadelphia: Pennsylvania University Press.\n* [[Alison Weir|Weir, Alison]]. (1999) ''Britain's Royal Family: A Complete Genealogy.'' London: The Bodley Head.\n* Weir, Alison. (2006) ''Queen Isabella: She-Wolf of France, Queen of England.'' London: Pimlico Books. {{ISBN|978-0-7126-4194-4}}.\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category}}\n* Heidi Murphy [https://web.archive.org/web/20080209175140/http://www.britannia.com/history/biographies/isabella_france.html Isabella of France  (1295\u20131358), Britannia biographical series]\n\n{{S-start}}\n{{S-roy|en}}\n|-\n{{S-vac|last=[[Marguerite of France (born 1282)|Margaret of France]]}}\n{{S-ttl| title =[[List of English consorts|Queen consort of England]]<br />[[List of Irish consorts|Lady of Ireland]]| years = 25 January 1308&nbsp;\u2013 25 January 1327}}\n{{S-vac|next=[[Philippa of Hainault]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{House of Plantagenet}}\n{{English consort}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Isabella Of France}}\n[[Category:1295 births]]\n[[Category:1358 deaths]]\n[[Category:13th-century French people]]\n[[Category:14th-century French people]]\n[[Category:14th-century English people]]\n[[Category:13th-century French women]]\n[[Category:14th-century English women]]\n[[Category:14th-century French women]]\n[[Category:14th-century women rulers]]\n[[Category:Duchesses of Aquitaine]]\n[[Category:Edward II of England]]\n[[Category:English rebels]]\n[[Category:English royal consorts]]\n[[Category:Founders of English schools and colleges]]\n[[Category:French princesses]]\n[[Category:French expatriates in England]]\n[[Category:French Roman Catholic religious sisters and nuns]]\n[[Category:House of Capet]]\n[[Category:Irish royal consorts]